<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871203-0082 </DOCNO><HL> Manufacturers HanoverOpens Operation in Tokyo</HL><DD> 12/03/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MHC JAPANSECURITIES INDUSTRY (SCR) </IN><DATELINE> TOKYO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Manufacturers Hanover Corp. said it opened an investment banking operation here.    The new unit, Manufacturers Hanover Securities Co., is a branch of Manufacturers Hanover Asia Ltd., which in September received full securities power in Japan from the Ministry of Finance.    The New York-based bank holding company also offers commercial-banking and foreign-exchange services here through a branch of Manufacturers Hanover Trust Co., as well as investment-management and trust-banking services through two other units. </TEXT></DOC>